@flamby, for me it is very important to understand the underlying literature. We use volume or dollars as a proxy for information. The idea is that if there is a volume spike then information has entered the system.

If you implement your reverse logic then this mechanism breaks down. The reason that ticks get dropped in the last bucket is because we havent received the signal to sample the data. Which is inline with the literature.

I dont see a particular problem with that, however if you elaborate then I can respond to specific point.
